       Node n = node3->next();
   }
   ```
   
   This prevents unchecked null dereferences from being scattered through the
   program and makes the list invariant clear: either a node may have no
   successor and callers must check, or the data structure should enforce that
   every node has a valid successor before exposing traversal operations.
